Sentencas: In the present study, the overall cell performance and local transport characteristics of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are numerically investigated by using a two-dimensional mathematical model.
Titulo: Effect of Cell Length on Performance and Transport Phenomena in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The conservation equations of mass, momentum, species, energy and charge are solved to describe the transport processes in fuel cells.
Titulo: Effect of Cell Length on Performance and Transport Phenomena in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The model validation has been performed by comparing the numerical results with experimental data found in the open literature.
Titulo: Effect of Cell Length on Performance and Transport Phenomena in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Effects of cell length and flow direction arrangement on temperature and species distributions are systematically investigated.
Titulo: Effect of Cell Length on Performance and Transport Phenomena in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It is concluded that the performance of SOFCs is significantly increased when the cell length is increased.
Titulo: Effect of Cell Length on Performance and Transport Phenomena in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In addition, the temperature and species distributions are also greatly affected by the cell length and flow direction arrangement.
Titulo: Effect of Cell Length on Performance and Transport Phenomena in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
